cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing the performance of next generation mobile cellular networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper introduces a lower bound for the system performance and uses mathematical frameworks to analyze effective capacity. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper investigates the performance of a system (cellular network) and proposes a scalable approach to analyze it. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing QoS in wireless systems which can be related to multimedia applications. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the least likely category as there is no mention of cryptography or security in the paper.
